.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-enroll - Bind this node to your org's Fabric by scanning a QR code


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel enroll [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Enroll connects this node to your AceTeam organization's Fabric.

.PP
It displays a QR code that you scan with the AceTeam app (or a phone camera).
Once you approve the device, the node joins your org's private mesh
(Headscale user org_), authenticated and scoped to your organization, and
appears in the Fabric dashboard.

.PP
This is the easiest way to add a freshly installed or booted Citadel node:
just run 'citadel enroll' and scan.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for enroll

.PP
\fB--new-device\fP[=false]
	Force fresh registration, ignoring any existing machine mapping

.PP
\fB--node-name\fP=""
	Set the node name (defaults to hostname)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Scan-to-enroll this node into your org's Fabric
  citadel enroll

  # Enroll with a specific node name
  citadel enroll --node-name gpu-rig-01

  # Force a fresh device registration (ignore any prior machine mapping)
  citadel enroll --new-device
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
